{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"How would you like to be better than you are?"},{"time":4000,"text":"Suppose I said"},{"time":6000,"text":"that, with just a few changes in your genes,"},{"time":8000,"text":"you could get a better memory --"},{"time":10000,"text":"more precise,"},{"time":12000,"text":"more accurate and quicker."},{"time":15000,"text":"Or maybe you'd like to be more fit, stronger,"},{"time":18000,"text":"with more stamina."},{"time":20000,"text":"Would you like to be more attractive and self-confident?"},{"time":24000,"text":"How about living longer with good health?"},{"time":27000,"text":"Or perhaps you're one of those"},{"time":29000,"text":"who's always yearned for more creativity."},{"time":32000,"text":"Which one would you like the most?"},{"time":36000,"text":"Which would you like, if you could have just one?"},{"time":38000,"text":"(Audience Member: Creativity.)"},{"time":40000,"text":"Creativity."},{"time":42000,"text":"How many people would choose creativity?"},{"time":44000,"text":"Raise your hands. Let me see."},{"time":46000,"text":"A few. Probably about as many as there are creative people here."},{"time":49000,"text":"(Laughter) That's very good."},{"time":51000,"text":"How many would opt for memory?"},{"time":54000,"text":"Quite a few more."},{"time":56000,"text":"How about fitness?"},{"time":58000,"text":"A few less."},{"time":60000,"text":"What about longevity?"},{"time":62000,"text":"Ah, the majority. That makes me feel very good as a doctor."},{"time":66000,"text":"If you could have any one of these,"},{"time":69000,"text":"it would be a very different world."},{"time":71000,"text":"Is it just imaginary?"},{"time":73000,"text":"Or, is it, perhaps, possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"Evolution has been a perennial topic"},{"time":79000,"text":"here at the TED Conference,"},{"time":82000,"text":"but I want to give you today"},{"time":84000,"text":"one doctor's take on the subject."},{"time":86000,"text":"The great 20th-century geneticist,"},{"time":88000,"text":"T.G. Dobzhansky,"},{"time":90000,"text":"who was also a communicant"},{"time":92000,"text":"in the Russian Orthodox Church,"},{"time":94000,"text":"once wrote an essay that he titled"},{"time":97000,"text":"\"Nothing in Biology Makes Sense"},{"time":100000,"text":"Except in the Light of Evolution.\""},{"time":103000,"text":"Now if you are one of those"},{"time":105000,"text":"who does not accept the evidence for biological evolution,"},{"time":108000,"text":"this would be a very good time to turn off your hearing aid,"},{"time":111000,"text":"take out your personal communications device --"},{"time":113000,"text":"I give you permission --"},{"time":115000,"text":"and perhaps take another look at Kathryn Schultz's book on being wrong,"},{"time":118000,"text":"because nothing in the rest of this talk"},{"time":120000,"text":"is going to make any sense whatsoever to you."},{"time":123000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":125000,"text":"But if you do accept"},{"time":127000,"text":"biological evolution,"},{"time":130000,"text":"consider this:"},{"time":132000,"text":"is it just about the past,"},{"time":134000,"text":"or is it about the future?"},{"time":136000,"text":"Does it apply to others,"},{"time":138000,"text":"or does it apply to us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"This is another look at the tree of life."},{"time":144000,"text":"In this picture,"},{"time":146000,"text":"I've put a bush with a center branching out in all directions,"},{"time":149000,"text":"because if you look at the edges"},{"time":151000,"text":"of the tree of life,"},{"time":153000,"text":"every existing species"},{"time":155000,"text":"at the tips of those branches"},{"time":157000,"text":"has succeeded in evolutionary terms:"},{"time":159000,"text":"it has survived;"},{"time":161000,"text":"it has demonstrated a fitness"},{"time":163000,"text":"to its environment."},{"time":165000,"text":"The human part of this branch,"},{"time":168000,"text":"way out on one end,"},{"time":171000,"text":"is, of course, the one that we are most interested in."},{"time":175000,"text":"We branch off of a common ancestor"},{"time":177000,"text":"to modern chimpanzees"},{"time":179000,"text":"about six or eight million years ago."},{"time":182000,"text":"In the interval,"},{"time":184000,"text":"there have been perhaps 20 or 25"},{"time":186000,"text":"different species of hominids."},{"time":189000,"text":"Some have come and gone."},{"time":192000,"text":"We have been here for about 130,000 years."},{"time":196000,"text":"It may seem like we're quite remote"},{"time":198000,"text":"from other parts of this tree of life,"},{"time":201000,"text":"but actually, for the most part,"},{"time":204000,"text":"the basic machinery of our cells"},{"time":207000,"text":"is pretty much the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"Do you realize that we can take advantage"},{"time":212000,"text":"and commandeer the machinery of a common bacterium"},{"time":215000,"text":"to produce the protein of human insulin"},{"time":218000,"text":"used to treat diabetics?"},{"time":220000,"text":"This is not like human insulin;"},{"time":222000,"text":"this is the same protein"},{"time":224000,"text":"that is chemically indistinguishable"},{"time":226000,"text":"from what comes out of your pancreas."},{"time":231000,"text":"And speaking of bacteria,"},{"time":233000,"text":"do you realize that each of us carries in our gut"},{"time":236000,"text":"more bacteria"},{"time":238000,"text":"than there are cells in the rest of our body?"},{"time":240000,"text":"Maybe 10 times more."},{"time":242000,"text":"I mean think of it,"},{"time":244000,"text":"when Antonio Damasio asks about your self-image,"},{"time":247000,"text":"do you think about the bacteria?"},{"time":251000,"text":"Our gut is a wonderfully hospitable environment"},{"time":253000,"text":"for those bacteria."},{"time":255000,"text":"It's warm, it's dark, it's moist,"},{"time":257000,"text":"it's very cozy."},{"time":259000,"text":"And you're going to provide all the nutrition that they could possibly want"},{"time":261000,"text":"with no effort on their part."},{"time":263000,"text":"It's really like an Easy Street for bacteria,"},{"time":266000,"text":"with the occasional interruption"},{"time":269000,"text":"of the unintended forced rush to the exit."},{"time":271000,"text":"But otherwise,"},{"time":274000,"text":"you are a wonderful environment for those bacteria,"},{"time":277000,"text":"just as they are essential to your life."},{"time":280000,"text":"They help in the digestion of essential nutrients,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and they protect you against certain diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"But what will come in the future?"},{"time":289000,"text":"Are we at some kind of evolutionary equipoise"},{"time":292000,"text":"as a species?"},{"time":294000,"text":"Or, are we destined"},{"time":296000,"text":"to become something different --"},{"time":298000,"text":"something, perhaps, even better adapted"},{"time":301000,"text":"to the environment?"},{"time":303000,"text":"Now let's take a step back in time"},{"time":306000,"text":"to the Big Bang, 14 billion years ago --"},{"time":309000,"text":"the Earth, the solar system,"},{"time":311000,"text":"about four and a half billion years --"},{"time":314000,"text":"the first signs of proto-life,"},{"time":316000,"text":"maybe three to four billion years ago on Earth --"},{"time":318000,"text":"the first multi-celled organisms,"},{"time":321000,"text":"perhaps as much"},{"time":323000,"text":"as 800 or a billion years ago --"},{"time":326000,"text":"and then the human species,"},{"time":328000,"text":"finally emerging"},{"time":330000,"text":"in the last 130,000 years."},{"time":333000,"text":"In this vast unfinished symphony of the universe,"},{"time":336000,"text":"life on Earth is like a brief measure;"},{"time":339000,"text":"the animal kingdom,"},{"time":341000,"text":"like a single measure;"},{"time":344000,"text":"and human life,"},{"time":346000,"text":"a small grace note."},{"time":348000,"text":"That was us."},{"time":351000,"text":"That also constitutes the entertainment portion of this talk,"},{"time":353000,"text":"so I hope you enjoyed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":357000,"text":"Now when I was a freshman in college,"},{"time":360000,"text":"I took my first biology class."},{"time":362000,"text":"I was fascinated"},{"time":364000,"text":"by the elegance and beauty of biology."},{"time":367000,"text":"I became enamored of the power of evolution,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and I realized something very fundamental:"},{"time":372000,"text":"in most of the existence of life"},{"time":374000,"text":"in single-celled organisms,"},{"time":376000,"text":"each cell simply divides,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and all of the genetic energy of that cell"},{"time":381000,"text":"is carried on in both daughter cells."},{"time":384000,"text":"But at the time multi-celled organisms come online,"},{"time":388000,"text":"things start to change."},{"time":390000,"text":"Sexual reproduction enters the picture."},{"time":393000,"text":"And very importantly,"},{"time":395000,"text":"with the introduction of sexual reproduction"},{"time":398000,"text":"that passes on the genome,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the rest of the body"},{"time":402000,"text":"becomes expendable."},{"time":404000,"text":"In fact, you could say"},{"time":407000,"text":"that the inevitability of the death of our bodies"},{"time":410000,"text":"enters in evolutionary time"},{"time":412000,"text":"at the same moment"},{"time":414000,"text":"as sexual reproduction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"Now I have to confess,"},{"time":418000,"text":"when I was a college undergraduate,"},{"time":420000,"text":"I thought, okay, sex/death, sex/death, death for sex --"},{"time":424000,"text":"it seemed pretty reasonable at the time,"},{"time":427000,"text":"but with each passing year,"},{"time":429000,"text":"I've come to have increasing doubts."},{"time":431000,"text":"I've come to understand the sentiments of George Burns,"},{"time":434000,"text":"who was performing still in Las Vegas"},{"time":436000,"text":"well into his 90s."},{"time":438000,"text":"And one night, there's a knock at his hotel room door."},{"time":440000,"text":"He answers the door."},{"time":442000,"text":"Standing before him is a gorgeous, scantily clad showgirl."},{"time":445000,"text":"She looks at him and says,"},{"time":447000,"text":"\"I'm here for super sex.\""},{"time":450000,"text":"\"That's fine,\" says George, \"I'll take the soup.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"I came to realize,"},{"time":459000,"text":"as a physician,"},{"time":461000,"text":"that I was working toward a goal"},{"time":464000,"text":"which was different from the goal of evolution --"},{"time":467000,"text":"not necessarily contradictory, just different."},{"time":470000,"text":"I was trying to preserve the body."},{"time":472000,"text":"I wanted to keep us healthy."},{"time":474000,"text":"I wanted to restore health from disease."},{"time":477000,"text":"I wanted us to live long and healthy lives."},{"time":480000,"text":"Evolution is all about passing on the genome"},{"time":483000,"text":"to the next generation,"},{"time":485000,"text":"adapting and surviving"},{"time":488000,"text":"through generation after generation."},{"time":490000,"text":"From an evolutionary point of view,"},{"time":493000,"text":"you and I are like the booster rockets"},{"time":495000,"text":"designed to send the genetic payload"},{"time":497000,"text":"into the next level of orbit"},{"time":499000,"text":"and then drop off into the sea."},{"time":502000,"text":"I think we would all understand the sentiment that Woody Allen expressed"},{"time":505000,"text":"when he said, \"I don't want to achieve immortality through my work."},{"time":509000,"text":"I want to achieve it through not dying.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"Evolution does not necessarily"},{"time":517000,"text":"favor the longest-lived."},{"time":519000,"text":"It doesn't necessarily favor the biggest"},{"time":521000,"text":"or the strongest or the fastest,"},{"time":523000,"text":"and not even the smartest."},{"time":525000,"text":"Evolution favors"},{"time":527000,"text":"those creatures best adapted"},{"time":530000,"text":"to their environment."},{"time":532000,"text":"That is the sole test"},{"time":534000,"text":"of survival and success."},{"time":536000,"text":"At the bottom of the ocean,"},{"time":538000,"text":"bacteria that are thermophilic"},{"time":540000,"text":"and can survive at the steam vent heat"},{"time":543000,"text":"that would otherwise produce, if fish were there,"},{"time":546000,"text":"sous-vide cooked fish,"},{"time":548000,"text":"nevertheless, have managed"},{"time":550000,"text":"to make that a hospitable environment for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"So what does this mean,"},{"time":558000,"text":"as we look back at what has happened in evolution,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and as we think about the place again"},{"time":564000,"text":"of humans in evolution,"},{"time":567000,"text":"and particularly as we look ahead"},{"time":570000,"text":"to the next phase,"},{"time":572000,"text":"I would say"},{"time":574000,"text":"that there are a number of possibilities."},{"time":577000,"text":"The first is that we will not evolve."},{"time":582000,"text":"We have reached"},{"time":584000,"text":"a kind of equipoise."},{"time":586000,"text":"And the reasoning behind that would be,"},{"time":588000,"text":"first, we have, through medicine,"},{"time":591000,"text":"managed to preserve a lot of genes"},{"time":593000,"text":"that would otherwise be selected out"},{"time":595000,"text":"and be removed from the population."},{"time":597000,"text":"And secondly, we as a species"},{"time":599000,"text":"have so configured our environment"},{"time":602000,"text":"that we have managed to make it adapt to us"},{"time":605000,"text":"as well as we adapt to it."},{"time":608000,"text":"And by the way, we immigrate and circulate"},{"time":610000,"text":"and intermix so much"},{"time":612000,"text":"that you can't any longer"},{"time":614000,"text":"have the isolation that is necessary"},{"time":616000,"text":"for evolution to take place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"A second possibility"},{"time":621000,"text":"is that there will be evolution of the traditional kind,"},{"time":624000,"text":"natural, imposed by the forces of nature."},{"time":629000,"text":"And the argument here would be"},{"time":631000,"text":"that the wheels of evolution grind slowly,"},{"time":634000,"text":"but they are inexorable."},{"time":636000,"text":"And as far as isolation goes,"},{"time":638000,"text":"when we as a species"},{"time":640000,"text":"do colonize distant planets,"},{"time":642000,"text":"there will be the isolation and the environmental changes"},{"time":645000,"text":"that could produce evolution"},{"time":648000,"text":"in the natural way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"But there's a third possibility,"},{"time":652000,"text":"an enticing, intriguing and frightening possibility."},{"time":655000,"text":"I call it neo-evolution --"},{"time":657000,"text":"the new evolution"},{"time":659000,"text":"that is not simply natural,"},{"time":661000,"text":"but guided and chosen"},{"time":664000,"text":"by us as individuals"},{"time":667000,"text":"in the choices that we will make."},{"time":669000,"text":"Now how could this come about?"},{"time":672000,"text":"How could it be possible that we would do this?"},{"time":675000,"text":"Consider, first, the reality"},{"time":678000,"text":"that people today, in some cultures,"},{"time":681000,"text":"are making choices about their offspring."},{"time":684000,"text":"They're, in some cultures,"},{"time":686000,"text":"choosing to have more males than females."},{"time":689000,"text":"It's not necessarily good for the society,"},{"time":691000,"text":"but it's what the individual and the family are choosing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"Think also,"},{"time":697000,"text":"if it were possible ever"},{"time":701000,"text":"for you to choose, not simply to choose the sex of your child,"},{"time":704000,"text":"but for you in your body"},{"time":707000,"text":"to make the genetic adjustments"},{"time":710000,"text":"that would cure or prevent diseases."},{"time":712000,"text":"What if you could make the genetic changes"},{"time":715000,"text":"to eliminate diabetes or Alzheimer's"},{"time":718000,"text":"or reduce the risk of cancer"},{"time":720000,"text":"or eliminate stroke?"},{"time":722000,"text":"Wouldn't you want"},{"time":724000,"text":"to make those changes"},{"time":726000,"text":"in your genes?"},{"time":728000,"text":"If we look ahead,"},{"time":730000,"text":"these kind of changes"},{"time":732000,"text":"are going to be increasingly possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"The Human Genome Project"},{"time":739000,"text":"started in 1990,"},{"time":741000,"text":"and it took 13 years."},{"time":743000,"text":"It cost 2.7 billion dollars."},{"time":748000,"text":"The year after it was finished in 2004,"},{"time":751000,"text":"you could do the same job"},{"time":753000,"text":"for 20 million dollars in three to four months."},{"time":756000,"text":"Today, you can have a complete sequence"},{"time":759000,"text":"of the three billion base pairs in the human genome"},{"time":761000,"text":"at a cost of about 20,000 dollars"},{"time":764000,"text":"and in the space of about a week."},{"time":766000,"text":"It won't be very long"},{"time":768000,"text":"before the reality will be"},{"time":770000,"text":"the 1,000-dollar human genome,"},{"time":772000,"text":"and it will be increasingly available for everyone."},{"time":776000,"text":"Just a week ago,"},{"time":778000,"text":"the National Academy of Engineering"},{"time":780000,"text":"awarded its Draper Prize"},{"time":782000,"text":"to Francis Arnold and Willem Stemmer,"},{"time":784000,"text":"two scientists who independently developed techniques"},{"time":788000,"text":"to encourage the natural process of evolution to work faster"},{"time":792000,"text":"and to lead to desirable proteins"},{"time":794000,"text":"in a more efficient way --"},{"time":796000,"text":"what Frances Arnold calls \"directed evolution.\""},{"time":800000,"text":"A couple of years ago, the Lasker Prize"},{"time":803000,"text":"was awarded to the scientist Shinya Yamanaka"},{"time":806000,"text":"for his research"},{"time":808000,"text":"in which he took an adult skin cell,"},{"time":810000,"text":"a fibroblast,"},{"time":812000,"text":"and by manipulating just four genes,"},{"time":815000,"text":"he induced that cell"},{"time":817000,"text":"to revert to a pluripotential stem cell --"},{"time":821000,"text":"a cell potentially capable"},{"time":824000,"text":"of becoming any cell in your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"These changes are coming."},{"time":829000,"text":"The same technology"},{"time":831000,"text":"that has produced the human insulin in bacteria"},{"time":833000,"text":"can make viruses"},{"time":835000,"text":"that will not only protect you against themselves,"},{"time":838000,"text":"but induce immunity against other viruses."},{"time":840000,"text":"Believe it or not,"},{"time":842000,"text":"there's an experimental trial going on"},{"time":844000,"text":"with vaccine against influenza"},{"time":847000,"text":"that has been grown in the cells of a tobacco plant."},{"time":851000,"text":"Can you imagine something good coming out of tobacco?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855000,"text":"These are all reality today,"},{"time":858000,"text":"and [in] the future, will be evermore possible."},{"time":861000,"text":"Imagine then"},{"time":863000,"text":"just two other little changes."},{"time":866000,"text":"You can change the cells in your body,"},{"time":868000,"text":"but what if you could change the cells in your offspring?"},{"time":872000,"text":"What if you could change the sperm and the ova,"},{"time":874000,"text":"or change the newly fertilized egg,"},{"time":877000,"text":"and give your offspring a better chance"},{"time":879000,"text":"at a healthier life --"},{"time":881000,"text":"eliminate the diabetes, eliminate the hemophilia,"},{"time":883000,"text":"reduce the risk of cancer?"},{"time":885000,"text":"Who doesn't want healthier children?"},{"time":888000,"text":"And then, that same analytic technology,"},{"time":891000,"text":"that same engine of science"},{"time":893000,"text":"that can produce"},{"time":895000,"text":"the changes to prevent disease,"},{"time":897000,"text":"will also enable us"},{"time":900000,"text":"to adopt super-attributes,"},{"time":902000,"text":"hyper-capacities --"},{"time":904000,"text":"that better memory."},{"time":906000,"text":"Why not have the quick wit"},{"time":908000,"text":"of a Ken Jennings,"},{"time":910000,"text":"especially if you can augment it"},{"time":912000,"text":"with the next generation of the Watson machine?"},{"time":915000,"text":"Why not have the quick twitch muscle"},{"time":918000,"text":"that will enable you to run faster and longer?"},{"time":921000,"text":"Why not live longer?"},{"time":925000,"text":"These will be irresistible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927000,"text":"And when we are at a position"},{"time":930000,"text":"where we can pass it on to the next generation,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and we can adopt the attributes we want,"},{"time":935000,"text":"we will have converted"},{"time":938000,"text":"old-style evolution"},{"time":940000,"text":"into neo-evolution."},{"time":942000,"text":"We'll take a process"},{"time":944000,"text":"that normally might require 100,000 years,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and we can compress it down to a thousand years --"},{"time":949000,"text":"and maybe even in the next 100 years."},{"time":952000,"text":"These are choices"},{"time":954000,"text":"that your grandchildren,"},{"time":956000,"text":"or their grandchildren,"},{"time":958000,"text":"are going to have before them."},{"time":961000,"text":"Will we use these choices"},{"time":964000,"text":"to make a society that is better,"},{"time":967000,"text":"that is more successful, that is kinder?"},{"time":970000,"text":"Or, will we selectively choose different attributes"},{"time":973000,"text":"that we want for some of us"},{"time":975000,"text":"and not for others of us?"},{"time":977000,"text":"Will we make a society"},{"time":980000,"text":"that is more boring and more uniform,"},{"time":983000,"text":"or more robust and more versatile?"},{"time":986000,"text":"These are the kinds of questions"},{"time":988000,"text":"that we will have to face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990000,"text":"And most profoundly of all,"},{"time":992000,"text":"will we ever be able to develop the wisdom,"},{"time":995000,"text":"and to inherit the wisdom,"},{"time":997000,"text":"that we'll need to make these choices wisely?"},{"time":1000000,"text":"For better or worse,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and sooner than you may think,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"these choices will be up to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}